  "prompt": "If you had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, what would you do?",
  "response": "If I had 3 years to live and $3 billion to spend, I would focus on maximizing the positive impact I could have during that time. Here are some key areas I would consider:\n\n1. **Philanthropy**: Allocate a significant portion of the funds to charitable organizations and causes that I am passionate about, such as:\n   - Global health initiatives (vaccination programs, healthcare access).\n   - Education (funding scholarships, building schools in underserved areas).\n   - Climate change (investing in renewable energy projects and conservation efforts).\n   - Social justice (supporting movements and organizations that promote equality).\n\n2. **Personal Fulfillment**: Spend quality time with family and friends, traveling to places I have always wanted to visit. Experiences would be prioritized over material possessions:\n   - Traveling to different countries to immerse myself in diverse cultures.\n   - Organizing meaningful gatherings with loved ones.\n\n3. **Invest in Innovation**: Support startups or projects that align with my values, particularly in fields like sustainable technology, mental health, or education.\n\n4. **Create a Legacy**: Establish a foundation or trust to continue the work I believe in after I'm gone, ensuring that the impact of my spending lasts beyond my lifetime.\n\n5. **Art and Culture**: Invest in the arts by funding scholarships for artists, commissioning new works, or supporting local cultural institutions.\n\n6. **Wellness and Research**: Use some of the money to collaborate with medical researchers to explore health and longevity, potentially contributing to advancements that could help others.\n\nUltimately, the focus would be on creating a meaningful impact while cherishing the time I have left.",
